name: HOOK, LINE, AND SINKER
description: -used to emphasize that someone has been completely deceived or tricked. This artwork also represents SELF SABOTAGE in a way;Behavior is said to be self-sabotaging when it creates problems in daily life and interferes with long-standing goals. The most common self-sabotaging behaviors include procrastination, self-medication with drugs or alcohol, comfort eating, and forms of self-injury such as cutting.
